 width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umocean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mocean</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 12:10:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19571.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling Gate rules</span><hr size=1> This is an excerpt from a merchant pricing guide on EQTraders.com called &quot;Everything You Always Wanted to Know About Merchant Pricing but were Afraid to Ask&quot; by Balidil Anla'shok. You can check the entire thing at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/prices/about_pricing.htm">www.eqtraders.com/prices/...ricing.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...any faction indifferent or better will get exactly the same prices for the same charisma. Doesn't matter if you're ally or sneaking so as indifferent as can be, it's all the same to the merchants.<br>
There are several crucial charisma numbers to shoot for. Key to this is that, whether your faction is apprehensive or indifferent or better, there's a stretch from 61 or 62 to 76 or 77 (I haven't been able to get a gear combination that gives any of my characters either 61 or 76 charisma yet, unfortunately) that gives exactly the same prices. So, if you can get your charisma up to 62, don't bother getting any more charisma boosters until you can get enough to get you to 76. However, when you do get to 76, the prices will suddenly drop by about 6%, instead of the 0.5% you get for most individual points of charisma. <br>
Better known is the &quot;magic number&quot; of charisma, 104. This is the point at which indifferent or better merchants will give you the best price they're ever going to give you. This price seems to be based on 1.05 times a &quot;actual value&quot; that you will never see used, but is only directly known by the server. For instance, many gem and metal prices are clearly based on this. And, if you notice the prices at which the vendor will buy such things back from you, although it looks like a very irregular number, for instance 95pp 2gp 3sp 8cp for a bar of platinum or a sapphire, that just happens to be 100pp divided by 1.05. <br>
The last and highest number to shoot for is 132. This is the charisma at which you can normally get the cheapest prices even with apprehensive faction. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Get yourself a pair of opal encrusted steins and a sarnak bracer of honor or two (if necessary) and knock yourself out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 12:23:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19571.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling Gate rules</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> any faction indifferent or better will get exactly the same prices for the same charisma<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->People keep saying this, but it's also simply not true. Maybe these people need to drop in CHA and see what happens to those of us under 75. There is an actual difference between indifferent and amiable.<br>
