<br>
Having played a bard to 55, I've found that when I would sing factionsong to improve my faction, I would see NO change in price offered. HOWEVER, this was at CHA that usually ranged from 115ish on the low end to 130+ on the upper end. I wouldn't rule out the possibility that faction can have an effect on pricing for those with low CHA which is lost (or buried) with high CHA until some tests are run on the SAME vendor at different factions.<br>
<br>
The reason that it is vital to test the same vendor is that different vendors on the same faction will offer different prices. Some merchants are just coded as 'bad' pricers (from our standpoint), some are 'neutral', some are 'good'. There are more than just 3 levels, even, from what I have observed. I've learned to test merchants in any town in which I wish to sell by running around &amp; offering for sell a reasonably high-priced item (so that even small differences can be detected). Note the offer, cancel, run to next merchant &amp; repeat. Even on something as cheap as a GLS, I've seen offers differ by almost 25% between the worst &amp; the best merchants -- &amp; again, this is at the same faction &amp; same CHA.<br>
<br>
So -- was the person who reported a difference in pricing from 104 CHA to 142 (or whatever it was) talking about the same vendor? Has Whizbang been checking the same merchants as he raised faction, or looking at different ones? Obviously I'm not going to think I've stumbled onto something unknown to the vastly experienced EQ player community, but given that it was a couple of years of play before I found this myself, I suppose it's possible others might have overlooked it as well... or then again, it could just be me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uholmiumelblastee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Holmium ElBlastee</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 3:15:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19571.topic&index=56>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/firestor/nzflag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling Gate rules</span><hr size=1> /bog<br>
